{"TopicId":131730,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Auto Screenshot option","CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-09T09:47:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-09T09:47:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s great to keep a record of our exploits by taking screenshots, but it\u0027s all too easy to get carried away with the moment and forget to hit F1, only to realise afterwards that it would have been a really cool photo.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo how about an Automatic Screenshot taker? \u00A0Simply set it up so that it automatically takes a screenshot at a regular time interval, which is settable by the player either with a \u00A0slider or textbox type input. \u00A0If its accessible from the Esc. Menu then it will be easy to toggle on or off, or change the timings, in play to enable you to increase or decrease the frequency depending on the situation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MircoMars","CreatedById":61811,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-09T09:50:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsounds like a great mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\non the title\u00A0I thought about auto-screenshots on achieving stuff. first flight, first crash, first\u00A0in-atmo-disassembly etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-09T10:05:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOffered for your consideration:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/116979-release-automated-screenshots-060-105-compatible/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-09T15:09:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222400510\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131730\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221455012331\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOffered for your consideration:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/116979-release-automated-screenshots-060-105-compatible/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust had\u00A0a\u00A0look at the link. I will give that a a try.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-09T15:14:51Z\u0022 title=\u002202/09/2016 03:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 9, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by pandaman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AbacusWizard","CreatedById":116476,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-09T19:53:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool idea. You could even set the interval to, say, 1/8 of a second to get frames for an animated gif.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-09T22:09:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI installed and tried it tonight.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt works well.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks again for the link\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}